\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 29. P. hirta} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 497 (1753). Like {\b 28} but stems and leaves with only long, patent, eglandular hairs; leaflets linear- to oblong-oblanceolate, rarely obovate, with 3-7 obtuse teeth or lobes at apex; petals longer than sepals. •{\i  W. Mediterranean region.} Co Ga Hs It.
