\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 37. P. longipes} Ledeb.,{\i  Fl. Ross.}{\b  2}: 50 (1843). Perennial. Flowering stems 15-50 cm, sparsely hairy. Leaves digitate; leaflets 7, 25-50 × 10-20 mm, oblong or oblong-obovate, coarsely toothed or almost pinnatifid, glabrous above, sparsely hairy beneath. Flowers usually numerous. Sepals ovate-lanceolate; epicalyx-segments linear-lanceolate, about as long as sepals. Petals c. 6 mm, yellow, longer than sepals. Style conical-filiform.{\i  S.E Russia}. Rs (C, E).
\par

